Derived elements retained from upstream:
  - Role framing ("final quality gate, not helpful assistant")
  - Four-phase investigation protocol skeleton
  - Multi-perspective review matrix
  - Gap-analysis prompt
  - Output format skeleton
  - Failure-modes-to-avoid list

Substantial additions by Hinano Hart (MIT, 2026):
  - Phase 6: Statistical Sanity Pass (S1-S7, derived from a personal
    research line's bootstrap-CI invalidation of an n=3 "all positive"
    illusion).
  - Phase 7: Post-Publication Adversarial Pass (P1-P6, derived from a
    side-project's post-release 8-agent parallel audit).
  - Phase 8: Anti-Pattern Detection (A1-A8, including frame-hopping,
    sunk-cost protection, narrative-fit bias).
  - Case Study Anchors (CS-1 through CS-6) drawn from real published
    research-code failures and their corrections.
  - Japanese translation of the agent prompt.
  - Repository scaffolding (docs, tests, CI).

